561
01:05:17,280 --> 01:05:20,841
When we were together,
you were so passionate
about becoming a lawyer.

562
01:05:20,950 --> 01:05:22,918
I mean, you were...

563
01:05:24,420 --> 01:05:26,320
very passionate.

564
01:05:26,422 --> 01:05:30,153
Yeah, well,
passion's a funny thing.

565
01:05:32,261 --> 01:05:34,661
<i>I have a doctorate</i>
<i>in animal behavior.</i>

566
01:05:34,764 --> 01:05:38,427
But that was
sort of after the fact.

567
01:05:39,969 --> 01:05:41,937
It's an odd story.

568
01:05:43,306 --> 01:05:45,740
I'm getting into odd stories.

569
01:05:45,875 --> 01:05:49,333
Well, I was a very successful lawyer.

570
01:05:50,947 --> 01:05:53,347
I had no life, though,
outside my work,

571
01:05:53,449 --> 01:05:56,111
except for my dog,
Winston.

572
01:05:58,421 --> 01:06:00,889
Your dog's named Winston?

573
01:06:02,091 --> 01:06:03,991
<i>Yes.</i>

574
01:06:04,093 --> 01:06:05,993
<i>But then he died...</i>

575
01:06:06,095 --> 01:06:08,063
suddenly.

576
01:06:09,598 --> 01:06:12,499
I'm sorry.
Oh, no.
It was, uh-

577
01:06:12,601 --> 01:06:14,501
It was years ago.

578
01:06:14,637 --> 01:06:17,902
But my new ability was this gift.

579
01:06:19,475 --> 01:06:21,409
This gift from Winston.

580
01:06:39,428 --> 01:06:42,056
All right,
you can come in again.

581
01:06:47,470 --> 01:06:49,404
Anyway,

582
01:06:49,505 --> 01:06:52,338
<i>after Winston died</i>
<i>I got this gift.</i>

583
01:06:52,441 --> 01:06:54,841
<i>To-</i>

584
01:06:54,944 --> 01:06:57,208
To read animals' minds?
<i>No. I told you-</i>

585
01:06:57,313 --> 01:07:00,612
- No.
- I'm a communicator.

586
01:07:02,685 --> 01:07:05,483
You see,
soon after Winston died...

587
01:07:06,756 --> 01:07:10,317
I realized that I could
hear animals speak to me.

588
01:07:10,426 --> 01:07:14,954
I mean, I certainly hadn't
been aware of that before.

589
01:07:15,064 --> 01:07:17,191
And I don't
read animals' minds.

590
01:07:17,299 --> 01:07:19,995
<i>But when they want</i>
<i>to communicate,</i>

591
01:07:20,102 --> 01:07:22,662
<i>I can hear them.</i>

592
01:07:22,805 --> 01:07:25,239
You know,
like you and I are talking.

593
01:07:25,341 --> 01:07:28,538
<i>But we don't</i>
<i>read each other's minds.</i>

594
01:07:33,315 --> 01:07:35,715
Is he saying something?

595
01:07:44,326 --> 01:07:46,794
He says
you have a hidden agenda.

596
01:07:47,863 --> 01:07:51,458
He- He said that?

597
01:07:53,636 --> 01:07:56,104
I think you'd better
go back outside now, Ramon.

598
01:08:04,647 --> 01:08:06,547
<i>Animals can tell us</i>
<i>what they want,</i>

599
01:08:06,649 --> 01:08:10,608
but that doesn't mean
that that's what's best for them.

600
01:08:13,989 --> 01:08:16,014
<i>Yes?</i>

601
01:08:17,827 --> 01:08:21,695
Excuse me, Carmen,
but Mr. Renaldo and Skippy
are here for your next session.

602
01:08:21,797 --> 01:08:23,697
Oh. Okay.

603
01:08:23,799 --> 01:08:26,859
Um, give me
one more minute.

604
01:08:37,613 --> 01:08:41,481
<i>Sorry, Don, but I really</i>
<i>can't keep Skippy waiting.</i>

605
01:08:41,584 --> 01:08:46,988
Do you think you could tell Skippy
that you're just gonna walk me to my car?

606
01:08:50,426 --> 01:08:53,327
How about later?
Wanna get a drink?

607
01:08:53,429 --> 01:08:55,329
No. I don't drink.

608
01:08:55,431 --> 01:08:57,331
Maybe get something to eat?

609
01:08:57,433 --> 01:09:00,266
I don't, uh, eat.

610
01:09:02,204 --> 01:09:04,104
You don't?

611
01:09:04,206 --> 01:09:07,107
Uh, take a walk?

612
01:09:07,209 --> 01:09:10,144
I know you walk.
I don't feel like it.

613
01:09:13,849 --> 01:09:15,749
Do you have a typewriter?

614
01:09:15,851 --> 01:09:17,819
A typewriter?

615
01:09:21,524 --> 01:09:24,084
Are you married?

616
01:09:24,193 --> 01:09:27,253
You know, I think you
should probably go now.

617
01:09:27,363 --> 01:09:29,331
Oh, come on, Carmen.

618
01:09:30,866 --> 01:09:33,027
Can't you answer me?
No.

619
01:09:34,403 --> 01:09:36,303
"No," you won't answer me?

620
01:09:36,405 --> 01:09:39,841
No, I'm not married.

621
01:09:41,944 --> 01:09:43,878
I was though.

622
01:09:45,814 --> 01:09:48,009
Any kids?

623
01:09:50,586 --> 01:09:52,554
Yes.

624
01:09:54,223 --> 01:09:57,249
<i>I have a daughter, Lianna.</i>
<i>She's 16.</i>

625
01:09:59,361 --> 01:10:01,261
She's in Sweden.

626
01:10:01,363 --> 01:10:03,422
Sweden.

627
01:10:03,532 --> 01:10:05,864
Am I supposed to ask
about you?

628
01:10:05,968 --> 01:10:08,903
<i>It seems like I've told you</i>
<i>my whole life story.</i>

629
01:10:09,004 --> 01:10:10,904
<i>So-</i>
Me? No.

630
01:10:11,006 --> 01:10:12,906
I'm not married.

631
01:10:13,008 --> 01:10:14,942
<i>Of course you aren't.</i>

632
01:10:16,912 --> 01:10:19,710
And I don't have any kids.

633
01:10:19,815 --> 01:10:21,783
Do I?

634
01:10:24,987 --> 01:10:26,955
How would I know that?

635
01:10:28,324 --> 01:10:31,885
Sorry, Carmen, but Mr. Renaldo
and Skippy have been waiting
in the session room.

636
01:10:31,994 --> 01:10:34,326
I know. I'm sorry.
I'll be right there.

637
01:10:34,430 --> 01:10:36,398
Okay.

638
01:10:43,239 --> 01:10:46,470
Well, my time is really up.

639
01:10:46,575 --> 01:10:49,806
So, good-bye.

640
01:10:49,912 --> 01:10:51,880
<i>Bye, Carmen.</i>

641
01:11:13,369 --> 01:11:16,896
<i>Mr. Johnston?</i>
<i>You forgot your flowers.</i>

642
01:14:27,930 --> 01:14:30,455
Hey. Excuse me!
Excuse me.

643
01:14:32,601 --> 01:14:36,435
Excuse me. Uh, do you know
where Atwood Road is?

644
01:14:36,572 --> 01:14:39,132
I'm lost.

645
01:15:58,220 --> 01:15:59,744
Oh!

646
01:15:59,855 --> 01:16:02,756
<i>Hey.</i>

647
01:16:02,858 --> 01:16:05,053
Hey, it's okay.

648
01:16:06,862 --> 01:16:08,796
It's okay.

649
01:16:09,831 --> 01:16:11,731
Can I help you?

650
01:16:11,833 --> 01:16:13,926
Does Penny live here?

651
01:16:14,036 --> 01:16:16,004
Who's askin'?

652
01:16:17,439 --> 01:16:21,933
I'm an old friend of Penny's.
Don. Don Johnston.

653
01:16:24,246 --> 01:16:27,738
She's in the house.
Go around there. A screen door.

654
01:16:27,849 --> 01:16:29,817
Thanks.

655
01:17:08,857 --> 01:17:10,825
Penny?

656
01:17:21,703 --> 01:17:23,637
Hello?

657
01:17:25,107 --> 01:17:27,632
- Penny?
- Yeah?

658
01:17:36,051 --> 01:17:38,019
Donny.

659
01:17:44,993 --> 01:17:48,156
So, what the fuck
do <i>you</i> want, Donny?

660
01:17:48,263 --> 01:17:52,461
Oh, I just thought I'd drop by.

661
01:17:52,567 --> 01:17:54,535
Just checking in.

662
01:17:57,639 --> 01:18:00,767
Well, I don't remember
any happy ending
between us, Don.

663
01:18:00,909 --> 01:18:04,811
No... reconciliation,
nothing.

664
01:18:04,946 --> 01:18:07,540
You left <i>me,</i> Penny.
Remember?

665
01:18:07,649 --> 01:18:10,083
Yeah.

666
01:18:10,185 --> 01:18:12,153
Very clearly.

667
01:18:15,023 --> 01:18:17,958
So, what is it you wanted?

668
01:18:18,060 --> 01:18:20,119
Everything okay over there, Pen?

669
01:18:21,963 --> 01:18:23,897
Not sure yet!

670
01:18:24,933 --> 01:18:26,901
Goddamn it.

671
01:18:28,036 --> 01:18:30,300
What is it you wanted?

672
01:18:33,975 --> 01:18:35,909
Penny, do you-

673
01:18:37,379 --> 01:18:39,347
Do you have a son?

674
01:18:46,421 --> 01:18:48,389
Fuck you, Donny!

675
01:18:56,798 --> 01:18:58,959
Danny, grab that fucker.

676
01:19:03,004 --> 01:19:04,938
<i>Penny!</i>

677
01:19:06,942 --> 01:19:09,308
Shut up.

678
01:19:09,411 --> 01:19:11,345
I didn't say anything.

679
01:19:32,367 --> 01:19:35,268
What the hell's
your fuckin' problem?
I was just leaving.

680
01:19:35,403 --> 01:19:38,770
No, what are you doing
upsetting Penny like that, huh?
I just needed to ask her a question.

681
01:19:38,874 --> 01:19:41,775
Yeah, I know
you asked her a question.
Now, listen.

682
01:19:41,877 --> 01:19:45,779
I just don't think
it's very sensitive of you...

683
01:19:45,914 --> 01:19:48,815
comin' out here
to try to hurt Penny's feelings,

684
01:19:48,917 --> 01:19:52,580
you know,
to get back at her or whatever.

685
01:19:55,390 --> 01:19:57,290
That just seems so rude.

686
01:22:23,605 --> 01:22:25,232
You said all pink, right?

687
01:22:25,373 --> 01:22:28,809
<i>It's best that they're all pink, yeah.</i>

688
01:22:34,649 --> 01:22:36,549
Oh, you're very good
at this.

689
01:22:36,651 --> 01:22:39,711
That's beautiful.
Thanks.

690
01:22:39,821 --> 01:22:41,721
Are you okay?

691
01:22:41,823 --> 01:22:45,725
Uh, it was just
a minor misunderstanding.

692
01:22:45,827 --> 01:22:48,694
Mind if I take a look?

693
01:22:52,834 --> 01:22:55,166
<i>Oh. That's nasty.</i>

694
01:22:55,303 --> 01:22:57,703
Did you even wash it?

695
01:22:57,806 --> 01:23:00,331
Sort of.

696
01:23:01,409 --> 01:23:03,343
Let me take care of it.

697
01:23:16,591 --> 01:23:18,491
What's your name?

698
01:23:18,593 --> 01:23:21,391
Sun. Sun Green.

699
01:23:21,496 --> 01:23:23,726
Sun Green?

700
01:23:23,832 --> 01:23:25,732
Perfect.

701
01:23:25,834 --> 01:23:27,734
What's yours?

702
01:23:27,836 --> 01:23:29,736
Don.
Don Johnston.

703
01:23:29,871 --> 01:23:31,839
Really?

704
01:23:31,973 --> 01:23:34,737
Don Johnson?
<i>Johnston.</i>

705
01:23:34,843 --> 01:23:36,777
With a "T."

706
01:23:39,047 --> 01:23:41,015
So...

707
01:23:45,320 --> 01:23:48,221
if I continue down this road,

708
01:23:48,323 --> 01:23:50,951
I will find
the Riverview Cemetery?

709
01:23:51,059 --> 01:23:55,257
