You'll see the entrance on your right.

710
01:24:01,736 --> 01:24:03,863
Thank you, Sun Green.

711
01:24:04,005 --> 01:24:05,939
You're welcome.

712
01:24:33,902 --> 01:24:35,870
Hello, beautiful.

713
01:25:43,471 --> 01:25:44,938
Red ink on pink paper.

714
01:26:16,804 --> 01:26:18,931
I don't know what I want.

715
01:26:19,073 --> 01:26:21,166
<i>He says you have a hidden agenda.</i>

716
01:26:21,309 --> 01:26:23,243
Fuck you, Donny.

717
01:27:23,371 --> 01:27:25,805
Circle Drive, please.
No rush.

718
01:28:10,985 --> 01:28:14,443
The wheel of fortune turns.
Round and round it goes.

719
01:28:14,555 --> 01:28:16,648
Where it stops, no one knows.

720
01:28:21,562 --> 01:28:23,530
Boy.

721
01:29:17,385 --> 01:29:20,218
That's my report,
Sherlock.

722
01:29:20,321 --> 01:29:23,290
The general outline
of what you put me through.

723
01:29:24,859 --> 01:29:26,759
That's it?

724
01:29:26,861 --> 01:29:31,230
And after all that,
you're still no closer to knowing
who's the mother of your son?

725
01:29:31,332 --> 01:29:33,300
That's right.

726
01:29:34,502 --> 01:29:36,993
But there was
that one typewriter.

727
01:29:37,138 --> 01:29:39,572
And the pink motorcycle.

728
01:29:39,707 --> 01:29:42,608
And it was Dora's pink,
uh, business card.

729
01:29:42,710 --> 01:29:44,871
And-And-And Laura's
pink bathrobe.

730
01:29:44,979 --> 01:29:48,415
I think this whole thing
is a farce, a fiasco.

731
01:29:49,450 --> 01:29:51,543
As far as I know,

732
01:29:51,652 --> 01:29:54,052
you may have written
that letter to me.

733
01:29:57,425 --> 01:30:00,826
Look, I'm really sorry
that you got beat up and everything.

734
01:30:00,928 --> 01:30:05,160
l-l-l-I feel that
it was somehow my fault.

735
01:30:05,266 --> 01:30:07,234
It was.

736
01:30:09,804 --> 01:30:12,068
Kind of strange, too, how, uh,

737
01:30:12,206 --> 01:30:15,141
Carmen's magic dog
was named Winston.

738
01:30:17,845 --> 01:30:20,245
Yeah-

739
01:30:20,348 --> 01:30:23,442
Look, man, I really put
a lot of work into this thing.

740
01:30:23,551 --> 01:30:27,453
I thought that it was
really important that you know
whether or not you had a son.

741
01:30:27,555 --> 01:30:30,820
I mean, it's your life.
You got to live your life, right?

742
01:30:30,925 --> 01:30:33,689
I <i>was</i> living my life,
Winston.

743
01:30:35,897 --> 01:30:38,297
I still am.

744
01:30:38,399 --> 01:30:41,493
What's this?
It's pink.

745
01:30:41,602 --> 01:30:44,537
It's a note
I found in my foyer
when I got back.

746
01:30:44,639 --> 01:30:47,699
Red ink on pink paper.

747
01:30:47,842 --> 01:30:49,673
It's from Sherry.

748
01:30:49,777 --> 01:30:51,677
What? From Sherry?

749
01:30:51,779 --> 01:30:55,112
Why didn't you tell me?
May I see it?

750
01:30:55,216 --> 01:31:00,347
Envelope and paper
not exactly the same size.

751
01:31:02,523 --> 01:31:04,753
You know, the handwriting...

752
01:31:04,859 --> 01:31:08,818
seems pretty close
to the address on the envelope,
but I can't be sure.

753
01:31:11,165 --> 01:31:13,133
Sherry still likes you.

754
01:31:15,770 --> 01:31:18,864
You think that Sherry
could have sent the first letter...

755
01:31:19,006 --> 01:31:22,203
and made the whole thing up
just to fuck with you?

756
01:31:22,310 --> 01:31:24,244
Who knows?

757
01:31:25,780 --> 01:31:27,680
You know, I've got to go.

758
01:31:27,782 --> 01:31:31,809
I think I have just enough time
to stop home
and compare the handwriting...

759
01:31:31,919 --> 01:31:34,945
and then hopefully
punch in at work on time.

760
01:31:35,056 --> 01:31:37,889
You coming?
No.

761
01:31:39,126 --> 01:31:42,152
I just need a little break
from all of this.

762
01:31:43,197 --> 01:31:45,097
Look, don't worry.

763
01:31:45,199 --> 01:31:48,066
We're still going to
solve this mystery.

764
01:32:39,587 --> 01:32:42,488
Didn't I see you
at the airport last night?

765
01:32:42,590 --> 01:32:44,649
I don't know.
Did you?

766
01:32:44,759 --> 01:32:46,659
Yeah.

767
01:32:46,761 --> 01:32:48,956
You on a road trip?

768
01:32:49,063 --> 01:32:51,031
Yeah.
Something like that.

769
01:32:54,735 --> 01:32:57,670
You look hungry.
Can I buy you a sandwich
or something?

770
01:32:57,772 --> 01:32:59,672
Uh, no, that's okay.

771
01:32:59,774 --> 01:33:03,039
You can relax.
I'm not gay. I'm not a cop.

772
01:33:03,144 --> 01:33:06,204
Just a guy who sees a guy
who might need a sandwich.

773
01:33:08,583 --> 01:33:10,551
Okay. Thanks.

774
01:33:11,652 --> 01:33:14,553
But could you get something to go?
I'd sorta rather stay outside.

775
01:33:14,655 --> 01:33:16,555
Sure.

776
01:33:16,657 --> 01:33:18,750
How about a nice
club sandwich?

777
01:33:18,859 --> 01:33:20,827
I'm vegetarian.

778
01:33:21,963 --> 01:33:23,988
You eat cheese?

779
01:33:24,098 --> 01:33:26,896
Yeah, sometimes.
l-I like cheese.

780
01:33:28,235 --> 01:33:30,703
Okay, I got it.
I'll be right back.

781
01:33:47,054 --> 01:33:48,954
Thanks.
You're welcome.

782
01:34:19,720 --> 01:34:21,688
Hey.

783
01:34:22,857 --> 01:34:25,519
You found us a place.

784
01:34:25,626 --> 01:34:27,719
All right.

785
01:34:31,098 --> 01:34:33,328
Let's see here.

786
01:34:33,434 --> 01:34:36,232
Big cheese and veggie sandwich...

787
01:34:36,370 --> 01:34:38,304
with mushrooms.

788
01:34:40,207 --> 01:34:42,107
Fries-
Mmm.

789
01:34:42,209 --> 01:34:44,143
extra large.

790
01:34:47,782 --> 01:34:49,750
Two waters.

791
01:34:52,653 --> 01:34:54,621
Two coffees.

792
01:35:03,197 --> 01:35:05,893
My mom put that there...

793
01:35:06,000 --> 01:35:07,968
<i>for good luck.</i>

794
01:35:12,606 --> 01:35:15,006
Thanks for the food.

795
01:35:15,109 --> 01:35:17,407
Ahh.
No problem, chief.

796
01:35:21,749 --> 01:35:23,717
You called me chief?

797
01:35:26,120 --> 01:35:28,088
Yeah. Why?

798
01:35:33,894 --> 01:35:35,862
What happened to your eye?

799
01:35:37,698 --> 01:35:39,666
I, uh-

800
01:35:41,469 --> 01:35:43,869
I ran into somebody.

801
01:35:44,004 --> 01:35:46,472
Somebody's fist.

802
01:35:48,309 --> 01:35:51,244
You a gangster?

803
01:35:51,345 --> 01:35:53,245
No. I wish.

804
01:35:53,347 --> 01:35:56,976
No, I was, uh-
I was in computers.

805
01:35:58,652 --> 01:36:00,620
Computers and girls.

806
01:36:02,656 --> 01:36:04,556
What about you, chief?

807
01:36:04,658 --> 01:36:07,684
I'm interested
in, uh, philosophy.

808
01:36:09,964 --> 01:36:11,932
Philosophy and girls.

809
01:36:16,070 --> 01:36:18,004
Sounds pretty good.

810
01:36:19,273 --> 01:36:21,707
Think so?

811
01:36:28,415 --> 01:36:30,383
So, uh,

812
01:36:32,052 --> 01:36:36,011
as just a guy
who gave another guy a sandwich,

813
01:36:38,759 --> 01:36:43,219
you have any, like,
philosophical tips or anything...

814
01:36:44,999 --> 01:36:48,093
for a guy on a kind of road trip?

815
01:36:49,170 --> 01:36:51,661
You asking me?

816
01:36:53,274 --> 01:36:55,208
Yeah.

817
01:36:56,343 --> 01:36:58,277
Well-

818
01:37:01,749 --> 01:37:04,479
The past is gone.

819
01:37:04,585 --> 01:37:06,553
I know that.

820
01:37:07,922 --> 01:37:10,584
The future...

821
01:37:10,691 --> 01:37:12,750
isn't here yet,

822
01:37:12,860 --> 01:37:14,828
whatever it's going to be.

823
01:37:16,363 --> 01:37:18,263
So,

824
01:37:18,365 --> 01:37:22,426
all there is is-
is this.

825
01:37:23,838 --> 01:37:25,772
The present.

826
01:37:31,812 --> 01:37:33,780
That's it.

827
01:37:36,150 --> 01:37:38,118
Are you a Buddhist?

828
01:37:40,187 --> 01:37:42,155
No. Are you?

829
01:37:43,691 --> 01:37:45,659
Uh, I'm not sure yet.

830
01:37:47,094 --> 01:37:51,497
I'm sorry that's the best
I have to offer at the moment.

831
01:37:51,599 --> 01:37:53,567
No, I appreciate it.

832
01:37:54,735 --> 01:37:57,203
I like what you said.

833
01:37:58,439 --> 01:38:01,806
It's better than some, like,

834
01:38:01,942 --> 01:38:04,069
fatherly-sounding bullshit.

835
01:38:07,448 --> 01:38:09,348
Is that...

836
01:38:09,450 --> 01:38:11,577
what your father's like?

837
01:38:18,325 --> 01:38:21,726
Ah, that's not a good subject.

838
01:38:21,829 --> 01:38:24,730
Hey, I gotta go, man.
I'm sorry.

839
01:38:24,832 --> 01:38:27,392
Thanks again
for the sandwich and stuff.

840
01:38:27,501 --> 01:38:29,492
Hold on a second.
Wait.

841
01:38:31,972 --> 01:38:35,533
I know you think
that I'm your father, don't you?

842
01:38:37,711 --> 01:38:41,112
What?
Just tell me.
You can talk to me, chief.

843
01:38:41,215 --> 01:38:43,479
Man, you're fucked up.

844
01:38:43,584 --> 01:38:46,212
Wait a second.
Wait a second. Wait!

